techmeme.title: Sources: TSMC and GlobalFoundries have finished negotiating agreements for billions of dollars in grants and loans under the CHIPS Act to support US factories (Mackenzie Hawkins/Bloomberg)
CRM software maker Freshworks plans to cut 13% of its workforce, or 660 employees, after reporting Q3 revenue up 22% YoY to $186.6M, vs. $181.6M average est. (Jaspreet Singh/Reuters)
Perplexity's US election hub offered helpful, real-time election insights and maps on November 5, linking to reliable resources and providing historical context (Maxwell Zeff/TechCrunch)
Australia plans to introduce legislation that would ban children under 16 from using social media, not exempting those already with accounts or parental consent (Maani Truu/ABC)
Take-Two reports Q2 net bookings up 2% YoY to $1.47B, vs. $1.43B est., net revenue up 4% to $1.35B, and sells its Private Division label to an unnamed buyer (Zaheer Kachwala/Reuters)
